%N A393694 Numbers that are sums of two positive cubes in two or more ways corresponding to the Pell-type equation X^2 - 3*Y^2 = 6318.
%H A393694 Jamal Agbanwa, <a href="https://figshare.com/articles/preprint/Generating_Infinitely_Many_Taxicab_Numbers_Expressible_as_the_Sum_of_Two_Positive_Cubes_in_Two_Distinct_Ways/30390145">Generating Infinitely Many Taxicab Numbers</a>, Figshare, (preprint) 2025.
%H A393694 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2716,-37830,2716,-1).
%F A393694 a(n) = x(n)^3 + y(n)^3 = u(n)^3 + w(n)^3 where:
%F A393694   x(n) = (-54 + 9*((15 - 7*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (15 + 7*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4 + 27,
%F A393694   y(n) = (-162 + 9*((7 - 5*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (7 + 5*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4,
%F A393694   u(n) = (-54 + 9*((15 - 7*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (15 + 7*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4, and
%F A393694   w(n) = (-162 + 9*((7 - 5*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (7 + 5*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4 + 81.
%F A393694 G.f.: 530712*x*(1387 - 38121*x + 2715*x^2 - x^3)/((1 - 2702*x + x^2)*(1 - 14*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Feb 25 2026
%e A393694 For n = 7, a(7) = x(n)^3 + y(n)^3 = ((-54 + 9*((15 - 7*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^7 + (15 + 7*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^7))/4 + 27)^3 + ((-162 + 9((7 - 5*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^7 + (7 + 5*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^7))/4)^3 = 285011938432925772595065675864.
